<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910110-0009</DOCNO><DOCID>910110-0009.</DOCID><HL>   International Brief -- Heckler andamp; Koch G.m.b.H.:   Merger With Giat Canceled;   Other Takeover Talks Begin</HL><DATE>01/10/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C11</SO><CO>   U.BA EUROP</CO><IN>TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)AEROSPACE (ARO)</IN><LP>   Heckler andamp; Koch G.m.b.H. of Germany, a financially troubledarms maker, said its agreement to merge into Giat IndustriesS.A. of France was called off. Terms of the December pacthadn't been disclosed.   Giat, an arms producer that is owned by the Frenchgovernment, said its chairman canceled the deal, because &quot;thenecessary conditions weren't fulfilled.&quot; Officials wouldn'telaborate, but they said the problems could involve thingssuch as closely held Heckler's financial condition, andregulatory requirements. Arms industry sources said Giat'sboard wasn't happy about financial terms of the deal andfinancial support required for Heckler, which is said to havebeen unable to meet payrolls last month. A Heckler-Giatmerger would have ended the uncertainty about Heckler'sability to continue in business and to introduce its new G-11series of rifle.</LP><TEXT>   Heckler said it began negotiations on a takeover by theRoyal Ordnance unit of British Aerospace PLC, and expressedoptimism about reaching an agreement after the end of thismonth.</TEXT></DOC>